<subSubSection pageId="35" pageNumber="36" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph pageId="35" pageNumber="36">Diagnosis.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="35" pageNumber="36">Head. Mandibles with 2 points. Prothorax. Pronotum with carina along lateral edge hidden or not in dorsal view; restricted to hind angles, or reaching less than halfway to anterior edge. Prosternum with anterior edge not short, produced as lobe, concealing labium when head not extended. Pterothorax. Scutellum with middle of anterior edge abruptly emarginate, anterolateral edges evenly rounded, and posterior apex pointed. Legs. No tarsomeres lobed or lamellate; tarsal claws with one apex per side. Also. Pterothorax. Brachypterous. Abdomen. Urosternites 3-7 without serrations along sides.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="35" pageNumber="36" type="type locality">
<paragraph pageId="35" pageNumber="36">Type locality.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="35" pageNumber="36">
Porto Santo Island, Madeira Archipelago, from a cave, females unknown. The relatedness of this species to brachypterous 
<taxonomicName lsidName="" pageId="35" pageNumber="36" rank="subfamily" subfamily="Cardiophorinae">Cardiophorinae</taxonomicName>
from the Canary Archipelago. and South Africa also placed in 
<taxonomicName genus="Cardiophori" infraspecific-rank="subgenus" lsidName="Cardiophori (Coptostethus)" pageId="35" pageNumber="36" rank="subGenus" subGenus="Coptostethus">subgenus Coptostethus</taxonomicName>
has not been demonstrated. Some 
<taxonomicName authority="Wollaston, 1854" authorityName="Wollaston" authorityYear="1854" class="Insecta" family="Elateridae" genus="Coptostethus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Metazoa" lsidName="Coptostethus" order="Coleoptera" pageId="35" pageNumber="36" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">Coptostethus</taxonomicName>
spp. from the Canary Archipelago have tarsal claws with 2 apices (Fig. 21), and would key here to 
<taxonomicName authority="Brulle, 1832" authorityName="Brulle" authorityYear="1832" class="Insecta" family="Elateridae" genus="Dicronychus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Dicronychus" order="Coleoptera" pageId="35" pageNumber="36" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">Dicronychus</taxonomicName>
. Includes 41 spp.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
